place.name: SYDE
place.gazetteerText: SIDE, or Syde, a parish in Cirencester district, Gloucester; 7½ miles NW by N of Cirencester r. station. Post town, Winstone, under Cirencester. Acres, 614. Real property, £886. Pop., 55. Houses, 11. The manor belongs to J. Hall, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of G1oncester and Bristol. Value, £126. Patron, J. Hall, Esq. The church is good. . (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
